    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "It looks like `ConvertTo-Json -AsArray 1,2` actually produces\r\n```\r\n[\r\n  [\r\n    1,\r\n    2\r\n  ]\r\n]\r\n```\r\nand not the expected\r\n```\r\n[\r\n  1,\r\n  2\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe `-ShouldBeLike` tests don't pick that up, but I played with them, and without maybe a switch on the `ConvertTo-Json` cmdlet to omit whitespace, I'm not sure how we would make them use `-ShouldBeExactly` cross-platform. Either that or a more complicated regex (not very in favour of that but it might be what we need).",
